## Phase 5: KPI Mode

Draft KPI definitions for the user's vertical. Include metric name, numerator,
denominator, time window, owner, and whether grounding is required.

Use these categories as examples, adapting to the user's business:

- Agentic AI operations: agent runs by hour/day/week/month, cron runs by
  hour/day/week/month, cron success rate, cron duration p50/p95, active agents,
  tokens in/out/total by period, estimated cost by period, cost per successful
  run, cost per workflow, human acceptance/edit/rejection rates, error rate,
  abort rate, task category resource mix, workflow repeatability, time saved,
  queue/backlog age if available, daily screenshot/report delivery status.
- Real estate: lead response time, lead-to-appointment rate, appointment-to-offer
  rate, offer-to-close rate, follow-up completion, listing-copy revisions, CMA
  turnaround time, showing coordination time saved, CRM enrichment completion,
  human edit rate, fair-housing review flags.
- SaaS: trial signups, activation rate, time to first value, feature adoption,
  support volume, churn-risk flags, MRR/ARR movement, demo booked rate,
  issue-to-PR cycle time, QA pass rate, deploy frequency, post-deploy incidents.
- Ecommerce: orders, average order value, cart abandonment, refund rate, support
  tickets per order, campaign approval rate, product-page copy revisions, return
  reasons, inventory flags, response time, upsell/cross-sell conversion.
- Agencies/services: inbound leads, proposal turnaround, proposal acceptance,
  onboarding completion, billable hours saved, revision cycles, follow-up
  completion, project status risk, invoice collection.
- Legal/finance ops: intake completion, document review turnaround,
  missing-document rate, risk flags, client response time, compliance review
  pass rate, human edit rate, matter stage movement, research memo acceptance.

Never infer regulated or sensitive attributes. Separate facts, estimates, and
assumptions.

